description:
Out of Control

Aired on 09/28/2005, Narrated by Jonathan Aris.

On 12 August 1985, Japan Airlines Flight 123, a Boeing 747SR, has an explosion during flight. The crew manage to keep the aircraft flying for 32 minutes until it clips Mount Osutaka and crashes, killing all but 4 people out of the 524 passengers and crew aboard.
